<DESCRIPT>  MOVIE; VIDEO; LIST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  MOVIE; CAPSULES  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Weekend  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  NEW
RELEASES  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>   (box) Bonfire of the Vanities  Tom Hanks is the yuppie bond trader whose
arrogance and privileged lifestyle collapse after he and his mistress (Melanie
Griffith) are involved in a hit and run accident. Bruce Willis and Morgan
Freeman co-star in director Brian DePalma's weak adaptation of Tom Wolfe's
novel. (Warner; rated R. Due Wednesday.);  (box) Marked for Death  Steven
Seagal in an action flick about a tough cop in a private war with a Jamaican
drug lord who attacked his family. (CBS/Fox; R. Due Thursday.);  (box) Night
of the Living Dead  Director George Romero's remake of his own zombie film has
none of the stark power or chills of the 1968 original. (RCA/Columbia; R. Due
Wednesday.);  (box) Pickup on South Street (1953)  Richard Widmark in a
classic "B" noir pulp flick, as a tough two-time loser who gets enmeshed in
espionage. (CBS/Fox);  (box) Gun Crazy (1949)  Brilliant noir cheapie, long
missing from video, about a tough female carnival sharpshooter who leads her
lover on a crime and killing spree. A genuine cult classic. (CBS/Fox);  (box)
Road House (1948)  Richard Widmark is a giggling psycho and Cornel Wilde the
business pal who steals his torch-singer chick (Ida Lupino) in this
marvelously sleazy, decadent trash. (CBS/Fox);  (box) The Glass Slipper 
Leslie Caron stars as a beautiful tomboy in this charming update of the fairy
tale. (MGM/UA);  (box) Challenge to Lassie  When Lassie's Scottish master is
killed, an old friend must convince an Edinburgh court to spare the grieving
dog. (MGM/UA);  (box) The Adventures of; Huckleberry Finn (1960)  Michael
Curtiz ("Casablanca") directed this first color version of Mark Twain's tale.
(MGM/UA);  (box) Peyton Place (195)  Lana Turner, Hope Lange, Russ Tamblyn and
Arthur Kennedy star in this milestone soap opera about passion in a small New
England town. Also available: "Return to Peyton Place" (1961), the sequel
starring Carol Lynley, Tuesday Weld and Jeff Chandler. (CBS/Fox);
MISCELLANEOUS; (box) Sinatra: The Reprise; Collection, Vol. II  150-minute
cassette set including three performances: "Sinatra" (1969); "Sinatra in
Concert at Royal Festival Hall" (1974); and "Sinatra: The Main Event" (1974).
(Warner);  (box) Your Mythic Journey  Bill Moyers PBS special with Sam Keen,
who discusses the importance of mythology in everyday life and spiritual
growth. (Mystic Fire);  (box) The American Indian; Collection  Five cassette
PBS series including such topics as "Geronimo," "Seasons of the Navajo" and
"The Spirit of Crazy Horse." (Pacific Arts);    (box) Dance Theatre of Harlem;
1987 NBC production of "Creole Giselle." (Kultur);    (box) Mr. Big: Hit
Singles; Collection; Music videos from the hard rock band. (A Vision)  </TEXT>
